    {
      "id": "1448811693747601538",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2025-12-11T23:00:25.409+00:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "No, that's on my to-do list.  I don't think I will be able to create a valid netlist for the 1kB SRAM without a schematic, though.  The existing netlists were generated with Calibre and are not schematic captured (and are, frankly, a big mess), so it needs doing and will get done when I get around to it.  For now I'm depending on the simplicity of converting the 512 byte layout to 1kB to be able to eyeball the LVS, but I hope to get proper LVS done before the Wafer.Space tapeout deadline passes.",
      "author": {
        "id": "1365118310701600900",
